                                                                                                                                                       Forms Tags
I - Meaning : are used to create forms that allow users to input data. 
II - Form Tags : 
    1 - Form : (<form>) This is the container for all form elements ( form block that sends data to a server )
	      Attributes		values							meaning
	      action			URL							Where the form data is sent
	      method			get / post					        How data is sent
	      target			_blank, _top, _parent, _self				Where to display response
	      autocomplete		on/off							Browser fills values automatically
	      novalidate									Disables validation on submit
	      enctype									        Type of encoding
	
    2 - Inputs : (<input>) "s" this tag is used to create various types of input fields, like text boxes, radio buttons, check boxes.
		1. Attributes		values			meaning
		type			#TYPES			Type of input
		name			string			Name of the input
		value			string		        Default value
		placeholder		string			Placeholder text
		required					Field must be filled out
		readonly					Cannot be changed
		disabled				        Unusable input
		checked					        Pre-select checkbox/radio
		multiple				        Allow multiple files/emails
		maxlength		number			Max characters allowed
		minlength		number			Min characters required
		pattern			regex			Pattern to match
		size			number			Width in characters
		autocomplet	        on, off			Autofill option
		min, max, step	numbers				Range constraints
		class			string			CSS class
		id			string			Used to link with <label>
		list			id of <datalist>	Show suggestions
		autofocus					Focused on page load (can't be more than a one in a page)
		form			id of a form		Associates input with form
		list			id of <datalist>	Show suggestions
						
		2. #TYPES		Meaning
		text		        Single-line input
		checkbox		Toggle on/off
		radio			Select one in a group
		password		Hidden characters
		email			Validates email
		tel			Phone number
		number			Numeric input
		range			Slider
		url			Web address
		search			Search field
		color			Color picker
		date			Date selector
		time			Time selector
		datetime-local		Local date & time
		month			Month selector
		week			Week selector
		file			Upload files
		hidden			Invisible data
		
	3  - Label : (<label>) This tag is used to define labels for form elements.
		Attribute		Values			Description
		for			id of input		Binds label to input
		form			form id			Associates with a form
		
	4 - Button : (<button>) this tag is used to create clickable buttons, often used to submit the form.
		Attribute				Values						Description
		type					submit, reset, button				Defines the action
		disabled, autofocus
		form, name, value			same as <input>
	
	5 - Text area : (<textarea>) This tag is used for multi-line text input
		Attributes					values		meaning
		name						string		Name for submission
		rows						number		Visible lines
		cols						number		Visible columns	
		placeholder, required
		readonly, disabled				same as
		autofocus form					<input>
		maxlength, minlength			
	
 6 - Drop down menu : (<select> + <option> + <optgroup>) :
	- <select> : 
		Attribute			Values		Description
		name				string		Field name
		multiple					Allow multi-select
		size	number					Visible options
		required, disabled		same as
		autofocus, form			<input>	
	- <option> : 
		Attribute			Values		Description
		value				string		Submitted value
		label				string		Alternative label (rarely used)
		selected					Preselected option
		disabled					Grayed out option
	- <optgroup> : 
		Attribute			Values		Description
		label				string		Group label
		disabled					Disable the group
	
	7 - <fieldset> + <legend> : Used for grouping related form elements
		- <fieldset> : 
			Attribute			Values		Description
			form				id		Associates with form
			name				string		Name (rarely used)
			disabled					Disables all inside it
		- <legend> : is used inside <fieldset> as its title
	
	8 - Datalist : Show suggestions ( Needs to be linked to an <input> using list="id" )
		<input list="ID">
			<datalist id="ID">
			  <option value="value1">
			  <option value="value2">
			  <option value="value3">
			</datalist>
	
	9 - Output : <output> Displays the result of a calculation
		Attribute	Values		Description
		for		list of ids	IDs of inputs it depends on
		form		form id		Binds output to form
		name		string		Field name
	
	10 - <meter> and <progress> : 
		- <meter> : Displays a known range of values (you must specify all values)
			Attribute			Values
			value				current value
			min, max			value range
			low, high, optimum		reference points
		- <progress> : Displays the progress of a task (like file upload)
		Attribute		Values
		value			completed value
		max			total value

